article.headline: Easly leads North Texas to 4th win, 47-7 over Liberty
article.description: Loren Easly rushed for 177 yards and two touchdowns as North Texas jumped out to an early lead and coasted to a 47-7 victory over Liberty on Saturday night to remain undefeated on the season.
article.linkText: Easly leads North Texas to 4th win, 47-7 over Liberty

images.name: North Texas WR jukes out defender for game's 1st score
images.caption: Jaelon Darden jukes a defender and scores to put North Texas up 7-0 early over Liberty.

video.title: North Texas WR jukes out defender for game's 1st score
video.description: Jaelon Darden jukes a defender and scores to put North Texas up 7-0 early over Liberty.

article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Loren Easly rushed for 177 yards and two touchdowns as North Texas jumped out to an early lead and coasted to a 47-7 victory over Liberty on Saturday night to remain undefeated on the season. Mason Fine hit Jaelon Darden on a 6-yard TD toss and found Rico Bussey Jr. on a 22-yard scoring strike to take a 14-0 lead in the first quarter. The Mean Green (4-0) pushed the lead to 21-7 at the half. The North Texas defense kept Liberty off the scoreboard in the second half while adding three more touchdowns, capped by Nic Smith's 66-yard burst for the final score. North Texas was coming off a 44-17 victory over Arkansas last week, its first win over an SEC opponent in more than 40 years. The teams faced a 42-minute lightning delay before the game and another short one in the second half. Fine threw for 185 yards on 16-of-27 passing with two touchdowns. Stephen Calvert led Liberty (1-2) throwing for 222 yards and one touchdown. Frankie Hickson rushed for 96 yards on 21 carries.
